Package edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.graph

Class EdgeListGraph<V,​E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.graph.AbstractGraph<V,​E>
      • edu.ncsu.csc316.dsa.graph.EdgeListGraph<V,​E>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of data in the vertices in the graph
    E - the type of data in the edges in the graph
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Graph<V,​E>
    public class EdgeListGraph<V,​E>
extends AbstractGraph<V,​E>
    An EdgeListGraph is an implementation of the Graph abstract data type. EdgeListGraph maintains a list of vertices in the graph and a list of edges in the graph. The EdgeListGraph class is based on the textbook: Data Structures and Algorithms in Java, Sixth Edition Michael T. Goodrich, Roberto Tamassia, and Michael H. Goldwasser John Wiley & Sons, 2014
    Author:
    Dr. King
